item.title: [tut] How to get runescapes hidden models with RSMV (2 sets discovered)
item.dc:creator: @CoonHunter CoonHunter
item.description:
@CoonHunter wrote:

[quote=“r r r, post:7, topic:283786”][quote author=CoonHunter link=topic=375053.msg2827127#msg2827127 date=1245111443]

Nice, but why are they hidden to begin with? And theres some strange models in here, like 79814.

yes, the number for this round goes up to a little over 111.2k I am in the process of finding more. BUt to answer your question, RS knows we can grab them. So they put some with High numbers, causing RSMV to not read them without some minor editing to the files. Mainly the reason that when there is a invalid model requested, RSMV stops and thinks it has finished. Editing it to start at 70k will cause it to read at the next start mark where they put models
[/quote]
Yeah and you know I have always thought the 47,000 models wouldn’t be all the models. Although I have seen some of the models in these new 70,000 plus files, some of them are the same as below 47,000. At first when I read this I thought the models might have something to do with HD.[/quote]
yes im notiving more and more HD items that are in the higher numbers lol. But there are some old items/landscapes. Just alot of very odd stuff that makes u go “wtf was rs thinking” lol
